Negative reviews are not my thing, but as a regular who has been displeased with their service before, I feel compelled to answer the Google review that popped up on my phone the next morning. 😁 Ordered my go to mega combo with curried goat and jerk pork with hot (scotch bonnet) and jerk sauce. The goat was mostly bones. The rice and peas was dry (the only gravy was directly under the goat). The entire container was filled with dry rice and steam veggies, with some goat, pork, and plantain.  Biggest disappointment though, was the pork. The pieces were so big and dry that a steak knife was required. The skin was inedible. There was maybe a teaspoon of the jerk sauce and no hot sauce.  Full credit to the lady who offered to replace it if I brought it back.

I wish I had the option to give no star. My first time doing uber eats with them. The experience was distraughtful. I am in shock of the poor customer service they provide. I ordered jerk chicken with rice and peas and a side of Mac and cheese which I had to pay an additional $2.00. I click on rice and peas and Mac and cheese only, because that is the option that is provided like any other Jamaican restaurant, for example “smoke house”, may I say, exceptional customer service especially over the phone. I received my food within 35 mins or so, which was okay with me. The speed of delivery was very effective. After I picked up my food from the driver, I looked in the container, it was jerk chicken alone and Mac and cheese on the side. I said to myself, maybe they misunderstood the order or something of that sort. I called with a mannerable and calm tone. Someone answered the phone and I start explaining the situation and she said “hol on, mi a go mek you talk to somebody, caz anno me do dah order deh” she didn’t even wait for a response or let me finish talking. Again that was okay too. She put me on the phone to talk to another woman and has I explained the situation, that I didn’t get my rice, she said she share what she saw and insinuated that I did not choose rice and peas. She did not try to help resolve the problem. I asked if I can come and pick up a side of rice and peas because I paid for it. It was a jerk chicken meal. I also paid for the side of Mac and cheese. She replied “mi cya help yo, tek that up wid uber”. I asked to speak with a manager and she responded “this is she”. I asked for her name and she told me her name is MARSHA. MARSHA, I must say, you have VERY POOR CUSTOMER SERVICE, that is a skill you definitely need improvement on. This was my very first time eating food from this restaurant and just because of this service, I will never recommend anyone to eat there. 1. The customer concerns will not be heard. 2. The problem will definitely not get solve. There’s no bad intention behind my review. I just want you to know, MARSHA (if that’s really your name) that your attitude was not pleasant. I spent $21.00 including uber fees on a quarter of chicken which was $11.00 and side of Mac and cheese for $2.00.

The oxtail order lacked flavor although the meat was tender. Same situation for the veggies like in the jerk meal. Then to top it off, the plantainnnn! You're either giving ripe plantain or don't bother. That thing was more green than anything and needed to be tostones.
